in #rstats 3.6 the following sets x as a numeric vector, in recent R it's a list. debugging around it made me pull my hair for way too long. I hope this helps.
x <- NULL
x[["a"]] <- https://t.co/0dYB0xsid3("2022-01-01")

`x[["a"]] <- 1` also creates a list & used to return num

just noticed `glue::glue()` can take named args, this is really cool :
glue::glue("{x} and {y}", x = 1, y = "a")
#> 1 and a
It looks a bit like:
sprintf("%s and %s", 1, "a")
Maybe better to have these explicit inputs when programming, for cleaner debugging/static analysis
